Step 8: Build a Project Management Board
Objective: Create a fully functional Kanban-style project management board with typed state management, drag-and-drop support, task CRUD operations, filtering, and dark mode — integrated with the existing dashboard and settings system.

---

Core Prompt:

Build a Kanban board application using React, TypeScript (strict mode, no `any`), and Tailwind CSS v3+. The board must support multiple columns, rich task cards, modal-based task creation and editing, real drag-and-drop interaction, filtering and search, and full dark mode support. Persist all board state to localStorage. Integrate with the navigation system (Step 2) and the dashboard layout (Step 3).

---

Architecture Requirements

Component Structure
    Implement the following component hierarchy:
        /components/kanban/
        ├── KanbanBoard.tsx           // Root container — owns board state
        ├── BoardColumn.tsx           // Individual column (header + task list + drop zone)
        ├── TaskCard.tsx              // Draggable task card with full metadata
        ├── TaskModal.tsx             // Shared modal for creating and editing tasks
        ├── BoardFilters.tsx          // Search bar + priority/assignee filter controls
        ├── BoardHeader.tsx           // Board title, add-column button, filter toggle
        ├── ColumnHeader.tsx          // Column title, task count badge, add-task shortcut
        ├── PriorityBadge.tsx         // Reusable priority label (Low / Medium / High / Critical)
        ├── AssigneeAvatar.tsx        // Avatar with tooltip showing assignee name
        ├── DueDateLabel.tsx          // Due date display with overdue styling
        └── types.ts                  // All shared TypeScript interfaces and enums

State & Data Model
    All state must be typed — no use of `any`.
    Define the following interfaces in types.ts:

        type Priority = 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'critical';
        type ColumnId = string;

        interface Assignee {
            id: string;
            name: string;
            avatarUrl?: string;
        }

        interface Task {
            id: string;
            title: string;
            description?: string;
            priority: Priority;
            assignees: Assignee[];
            dueDate?: string;          // ISO 8601 date string
            columnId: ColumnId;
            createdAt: string;
            order: number;             // position within its column
            tags?: string[];
        }

        interface Column {
            id: ColumnId;
            title: string;
            color?: string;            // accent color for the column header
            taskLimit?: number;        // optional WIP limit
        }

        interface BoardState {
            columns: Column[];
            tasks: Task[];
        }

    Default columns on first load: "To Do", "In Progress", "In Review", "Done".
    Persist BoardState to localStorage on every change.
    Load persisted state on initialization; fall back to defaults if absent.

---

Feature Requirements

1. Kanban Columns
    Display all columns side-by-side in a horizontally scrollable container.
    Each column header shows:
        - Column title (editable inline on double-click)
        - Task count badge (e.g., "3 tasks")
        - WIP limit warning when taskLimit is exceeded (highlight column header in amber)
        - An "Add task" icon button
    Columns must accept dropped tasks and reorder them accordingly.
    Provide a "Add Column" button in the board header that opens an inline input.
    Allow column deletion (only if empty; show a tooltip warning if not).

2. Task Cards
    Each TaskCard must display:
        - Title (truncated at 2 lines with ellipsis)
        - Priority badge with color coding:
            low → green, medium → yellow, high → orange, critical → red
        - Assignee avatar(s) (stack up to 3; show "+N" overflow badge)
        - Due date label — show in red with a warning icon if overdue
        - Tag chips (if any)
        - A drag handle icon (visible on hover)
    Clicking a card opens TaskModal in edit mode.
    Cards must have a visible hover state and smooth lift effect (shadow + slight scale).

3. Task Modal (Create & Edit)
    A single TaskModal component handles both create and edit flows, controlled by a `mode: 'create' | 'edit'` prop.
    Fields:
        - Title (required, max 120 characters)
        - Description (optional, textarea, max 500 characters)
        - Priority (dropdown: Low / Medium / High / Critical)
        - Assignees (multi-select from a static list of team members)
        - Due Date (date picker input)
        - Tags (comma-separated free-text input)
        - Target Column (dropdown — pre-filled based on where "Add task" was triggered)
    Behaviors:
        - "Save" button disabled until title is non-empty
        - Show a character counter beneath Title and Description
        - On save, generate a unique task ID using crypto.randomUUID()
        - On edit, update the existing task in-place
        - Confirm before discarding unsaved changes (show inline warning)
        - Trap focus within the modal; close on Escape or backdrop click
    Accessibility:
        - role="dialog", aria-modal="true", aria-labelledby pointing to the modal title
        - All form fields have associated <label> elements
        - Error messages use aria-describedby

4. Drag-and-Drop (Native HTML5 — No External Library Required)
    Use the native HTML5 Drag and Drop API (draggable, onDragStart, onDragOver, onDrop).
    Behavior:
        - Dragging a card highlights the destination column drop zone (dashed border + background tint)
        - Dropping a card into a new column updates its columnId and reorders by drop position
        - Reordering within the same column is supported
        - If the destination column has a taskLimit and is at capacity, reject the drop and show a toast notification: "Column is at WIP limit"
        - Preserve order values after every drop
    Visual feedback:
        - The dragged card renders at reduced opacity (opacity-50)
        - A drop indicator line appears between cards at the insertion point

5. Filter & Search
    BoardFilters renders a search bar and filter dropdowns, controlled by centralized filter state in KanbanBoard.
    Filters:
        - Text search: matches task title or description (case-insensitive)
        - Priority: multi-select (All / Low / Medium / High / Critical)
        - Assignee: single-select dropdown from available assignees
        - Due date: "Overdue only" toggle
    Behavior:
        - Filters apply in real time (no "Apply" button needed)
        - Filtered-out cards are hidden; empty columns show a "No matching tasks" placeholder
        - A "Clear Filters" button resets all filters
        - The active filter count is shown as a badge on the filter toggle button

---

UI/UX Requirements

Styling Consistency
    Maintain design token alignment with previous steps:
        rounded-2xl, shadow-md, hover:shadow-lg, transition-all duration-300
    Column width: fixed at 280px min-width with horizontal scroll on the board container
    Board background: a subtle grid or dot pattern using Tailwind's bg-dot or a custom utility class

Dark Mode
    Use Tailwind's dark: utilities throughout
    Sync with the theme persistence established in Step 4 (AppearanceSettings)
    Ensure all priority colors, column accents, and avatar backgrounds remain accessible in dark mode

Responsive Behavior
    Mobile (< 640px): show one column at a time with left/right swipe (CSS scroll-snap)
    Tablet (640px–1024px): show two columns; horizontally scrollable
    Desktop (> 1024px): all columns visible side-by-side with horizontal scroll

Animations & Transitions
    Modal enter/exit: fade + scale (transition-opacity, transition-transform, duration-200)
    Card drag: opacity drop on drag start, smooth position snap on drop
    Column highlight: transition-colors duration-150 on drag-over
    WIP limit warning: pulse animation on the column header badge

---

Advanced Challenges

These must be implemented as full features, not placeholders:

A. Column Management
    Allow adding new columns via the BoardHeader "Add Column" button:
        - Inline input appears; confirm with Enter, cancel with Escape
        - Assign a unique ID and a random accent color from a preset palette
    Allow renaming columns via inline double-click edit on ColumnHeader
    Allow deleting empty columns (with a confirmation tooltip)
    Allow reordering columns by dragging the ColumnHeader (drag handle visible on hover)

B. Task Assignment Feature
    Maintain a static roster of team members in a `teamMembers.ts` constants file:
        interface TeamMember { id: string; name: string; avatarUrl?: string; }
    In TaskModal, provide a multi-select assignee picker:
        - Displays avatar + name for each member
        - Supports keyboard navigation and selection
        - Selected assignees appear as stacked avatars in the TaskCard
    In BoardFilters, the Assignee filter dropdown is populated from this roster

C. localStorage Persistence
    Serialize and persist the full BoardState (columns + tasks) to localStorage under the key `kanban_board_state`
    On mount, deserialize and validate the stored state:
        - If invalid or corrupted, fall back to defaults and log a console warning
        - Use a version key (`kanban_board_version: '1'`) to handle future migrations
    Provide a "Reset Board" button in BoardHeader (with confirmation) that clears storage and restores defaults

D. WIP Limits
    Each column optionally accepts a taskLimit: number
    Display the current count vs. limit in the column header: e.g., "In Progress (3/5)"
    When the count equals the limit:
        - Color the badge amber
        - Disable the "Add Task" button for that column
        - Reject drag-and-drop drops with a toast notification

E. Toast Notification System
    Implement a lightweight toast system (no external library):
        /components/ui/
        └── ToastProvider.tsx     // Context + portal-rendered toast container
    Toast types: success, error, warning, info
    Auto-dismiss after 3 seconds with a progress bar
    Show toasts for:
        - Task created / updated / deleted
        - WIP limit exceeded (drag rejected)
        - Board reset confirmed
        - State load failure (fallback to defaults)

---

Acceptance Criteria

Core Features:
    [ ] All four default columns render correctly with titles, task counts, and add-task controls
    [ ] TaskCard displays title, priority badge, assignee avatars, due date, and tags
