Step 9: Create a Social Media Feed
Objective: Build a fully interactive social media feed with post creation, rich post cards, threaded comments, engagement interactions, and an infinite scroll mechanism — integrated with the existing navigation system, dashboard layout, and dark mode settings.

---

Core Prompt:

Build a social media feed application using React, TypeScript (strict mode, no `any`), and Tailwind CSS v3+. The feed must support creating posts with text and optional images, rendering a scrollable list of post cards with full engagement controls (like, comment, share), collapsible threaded comment sections, and an infinite scroll placeholder that simulates loading additional posts. Persist feed state to localStorage. Integrate with the navigation system (Step 2) and the dashboard layout (Step 3).

---

Architecture Requirements

Component Structure
    Implement the following component hierarchy:
        /components/feed/
        ├── Feed.tsx                  // Root container — owns feed state and scroll logic
        ├── PostCard.tsx              // Individual post card with full engagement controls
        ├── PostHeader.tsx            // Avatar, username, timestamp, and post options menu
        ├── PostMedia.tsx             // Optional image/video media display with aspect-ratio container
        ├── PostActions.tsx           // Like, Comment, Share action buttons with counts
        ├── CommentSection.tsx        // Collapsible threaded comment list for a given post
        ├── CommentItem.tsx           // Single comment row with avatar, author, text, and like action
        ├── CommentInput.tsx          // Inline reply/comment input with submit button
        ├── CreatePost.tsx            // Post creation form (text + optional image upload preview)
        ├── UserAvatar.tsx            // Reusable circular avatar with fallback initials
        ├── InfiniteScrollTrigger.tsx // Intersection Observer sentinel that fires a load callback
        └── types.ts                  // All shared TypeScript interfaces and enums

State & Data Model
    All state must be typed — no use of `any`.
    Define the following interfaces in types.ts:

        interface Author {
            id: string;
            name: string;
            username: string;       // e.g. "@jane_doe"
            avatarUrl?: string;
        }

        interface Comment {
            id: string;
            postId: string;
            author: Author;
            content: string;
            createdAt: string;      // ISO 8601
            likeCount: number;
            likedByCurrentUser: boolean;
        }

        interface Post {
            id: string;
            author: Author;
            content: string;
            mediaUrl?: string;      // optional image URL
            createdAt: string;      // ISO 8601
            likeCount: number;
            likedByCurrentUser: boolean;
            commentCount: number;
            shareCount: number;
            comments: Comment[];
            isCommentsOpen: boolean;
        }

        interface FeedState {
            posts: Post[];
            page: number;
            hasMore: boolean;
            isLoading: boolean;
        }

        interface NewPostDraft {
            content: string;
            mediaPreviewUrl?: string;
        }

    Seed the feed with at least 6 realistic mock posts on first load.
    Persist FeedState to localStorage under the key `social_feed_state` on every change.
    Load persisted state on initialization; fall back to mock seed data if absent or invalid.

---

Feature Requirements

1. Post Creation (CreatePost)
    A sticky card at the top of the feed with:
        - Current user avatar (left-aligned)
        - Expandable textarea: placeholder "What's on your mind?" (max 280 characters)
        - Character counter that turns red when ≥ 260 characters
        - Image attachment button: opens a file picker limited to image/* types
            - Display a thumbnail preview below the textarea; allow removal
        - "Post" submit button:
            - Disabled when content is empty and no image is attached
            - Shows a spinner during the simulated async save (500 ms delay)
        - On submit: prepend new post to the top of the feed, clear the form, show a success toast
    Accessibility:
        - textarea has an associated <label> (visually hidden is acceptable)
        - submit button has aria-disabled when inactive
        - image preview has a descriptive alt attribute

2. Post Cards (PostCard)
    Each PostCard must display:
        - PostHeader: avatar, display name, @username, relative timestamp (e.g., "2 h ago"), and a ⋯ options menu (Delete post for current user's own posts)
        - Post text content with "See more / See less" toggle for content exceeding 3 lines
        - PostMedia: full-width image with object-cover and a rounded-xl container (only when mediaUrl is present)
        - A divider line above PostActions
        - PostActions: three buttons — Like, Comment, Share — each showing an icon and a count label
    Hover & interaction states:
        - Card: subtle hover:shadow-lg and transition-shadow duration-300
        - Action buttons: icon color changes on hover; Like button fills/unfills on toggle
    Clicking the Comment button toggles CommentSection visibility (isCommentsOpen)
    Clicking the Share button copies the post URL to clipboard and shows a brief "Link copied!" toast

3. Comment Section (CommentSection + CommentItem + CommentInput)
    Collapsible per post, controlled by isCommentsOpen on the Post object.
    Rendering:
        - Show up to 3 comments initially; a "View all N comments" link loads the rest
        - Each CommentItem shows: avatar, bold author name, comment text, relative timestamp, and a like icon with count
        - Liking a comment toggles likedByCurrentUser and increments/decrements likeCount in state
    CommentInput:
        - Sits at the bottom of the open section
        - Single-line input with placeholder "Write a comment…" and a Send icon button
        - Submitting appends the new comment to the post's comments array and increments commentCount
        - Input clears after submit; focus is restored to the input field
    Empty state: when a post has no comments, show "Be the first to comment."

4. Like / Unlike Posts (PostActions)
    Clicking the Like button:
        - Toggles likedByCurrentUser on the Post
        - Increments or decrements likeCount accordingly
        - Animates the heart icon with a brief scale-up (scale-125 → scale-100, duration-150)
    State changes persist immediately to localStorage

5. Infinite Scroll (InfiniteScrollTrigger)
    Place an InfiniteScrollTrigger sentinel element below the last PostCard.
    Use the Intersection Observer API to detect when the sentinel enters the viewport.
    On intersection:
        - Set isLoading: true and render 3 skeleton PostCard placeholders (animate-pulse)
        - Simulate a 1 200 ms async fetch delay
        - Append 4 new mock posts to the feed
        - Increment page; set hasMore: false after page 5 to stop loading
        - When hasMore is false, replace the sentinel with "You're all caught up 🎉"
    Skeleton cards must match the layout of real PostCards to prevent layout shift.

6. Post Options Menu (PostHeader)
    A ⋯ icon button on every post opens a small dropdown positioned with Tailwind absolute utilities.
    For the current user's own posts: show "Delete post"
        - Clicking Delete shows an inline confirmation ("Are you sure?") before removing the post
        - Deletion updates state and shows a toast: "Post deleted"
    For other users' posts: show "Report post" (logs to console; no further action required)
    The menu closes when clicking outside (use a useEffect with a document click listener)
    Accessibility: button has aria-haspopup="menu", aria-expanded, and the menu has role="menu"

